xerography.n.01.wn_definition: forming an image by the action of light on a specially coated charged plate; the latent image is developed with powders that adhere only to electrically charged areas

xeroradiography.n.01.wn_definition: radiography using x-rays and xerographic (rather than roentgenographic) techniques

yoga.n.02.wn_definition: a system of exercises practiced as part of the hindu discipline to promote control of the body and mind

youth_movement.n.01.wn_definition: political or religious or social reform movement or agitation consisting chiefly of young people

zakat.n.01.wn_definition: the fourth pillar of islam is almsgiving as an act of worship

zap.n.01.wn_definition: a sudden event that imparts energy or excitement, usually with a dramatic impact

zero-sum_game.n.01.wn_definition: a game in which the total of all the gains and losses is zero

zero-tolerance_policy.n.01.wn_definition: any policy that allows no exception

ziegfeld_follies.n.01.wn_definition: a series of extravagant revues produced by flo ziegfeld

zing.n.01.wn_definition: a brief high-pitched buzzing or humming sound

zionism.n.01.wn_definition: a policy for establishing and developing a national homeland for jews in palestine

zodiacal_light.n.01.wn_definition: a luminous tract in the sky; a reflection of sunlight from cosmic dust in the plane of the ecliptic; visible just before sunrise and just after sunset

zone_fire.n.01.wn_definition: artillery or mortar fire delivered in a constant direction at several quadrant elevations

zoning.n.01.wn_definition: dividing an area into zones or sections reserved for different purposes such as residence and business and manufacturing etc

zoomorphism.n.01.wn_definition: the attribution of animal forms or qualities to a god

zymosis.n.02.wn_definition: (medicine) the development and spread of an infectious disease (especially one caused by a fungus)
